description.value: 'Kohl' tube of plam-column form: the  hollow shaft is of translucent dark-blue glass, its base outlined with a yellow thread. The lower body is decorated with two lines of chevrons in white and turquoise-blue. A turquoise-blue thread encircles the upper shaft six times. White threads outline the individual elements of the palm-leaf capital while the rim of the opening has a single turquoise-blue thread. The core is red-brown and retains faint traces of a fabric pattern. A slight chip on the capital is the sole damage. Also wooden 'kohl'-stick with bulbous head.
